Although several Hamas leaders are killed and the 1.7 million inhabitants of the Gaza Strip are infiltrated in one of the most desolate and densely populated corners of the planet, Israel has not yet succeeded in destroying Hamas.
In fact, Hamas is gaining in the West Bank, which is controlled by the rival, moderate Palestinian group Fatah.
