At least for a while, Israel will be able to sleep more calmly.
In diplomatic terms, the United States remains steadfast in its position, and many European countries have blamed Hamas for the recent escalation of violence.
Israel has done well in recent years, especially under Prime Minister Binyamin Netanyahu, who has largely ignored the peace process.
Although rockets from the Gaza Strip have killed about 30 Israelis since 2004, the country has remained relatively free from suicide bombers - not least thanks to the barriers that flow into the West Bank and thus into the main part of a possible Palestinian state. However, these protect the Jewish settlements, which have been declared illegal by international law, are constantly being developed.
Netanyahu is well standing. His Likud party has allied itself with an even more militant group in the run-up to the elections on 22 January under Avigdor Lieberman.
Why also these deceitful Palestinians pamper and leave them a state of their own?
