"This would affect the health of every human being," he added.
Correa stated that the solution to the asylum granted to Assange since June in the Embassy of Ecuador in London was the granting of a free letter, which allowed him to travel to Ecuador, and that this was in the hands of Britain, Sweden and the legal authorities of Europe. He stressed that there had been talks with London to find a solution for the imprisoned founder of WikiLeaks.
