While the judge of the case points out that creditors must be subject to the bankruptcy law of the United States, the Court of Appeals of the Fifth Circuit, based in New Orleans, first of all says that the main proceedings are the trade course dealt with in Mexico.
The first point would mean that international cooperation in insolvency proceedings of companies with a cross-border profile is not known.
